Pismo Coast Village RV Resort 
		

Welcome to paradise on the ocean 
		










An Award Winning Beachfront RV Resort 
		


 







Request A Reservation Now!MAKE RESERVATION!


PISMO COAST VILLAGE RV RESORTA Unique RV Camping Paradise on the Ocean
Situated midway between San Francisco and Los Angeles in beautiful Pismo Beach, Pismo Coast Village RV Resort needs only to be seen to be appreciated. Beautifully landscaped and nestled right on Pismo Beach (currently Pismo Creek is flowing along the resort and it is necessary to walk around the lagoon to get to the ocean), it is truly an outstanding destination RV resort. This award winning, nationally recognized resort is conveniently located within walking distance from downtown Pismo Beach shopping, restaurants, and the famous Pismo Pier.
Pismo Coast Village RV Resort features 400 full hookup sites, each with complimentary wireless internet access and cable TV , on 26 acres. Pismo Coast Village RV Resort also offers many great amenities including a General Store, restaurant, heated pool, arcade, laundromat, bicycle rentals, and miniature golf.
Relax to the sound of the surf, scent of the salt air, and the feel of an ocean breeze. It won’t take long to find you have discovered a unique RV camping paradise on the ocean.
Check out what is happening today at Pismo Coast Village RV Resort in Pismo Beach, California
Live Webcams and Virtual Tours:
username: pcv       password: since1975
Square Cam | Pier Cam | MiniGolf/Beach Cam
New recorded virtual tours 





Come enjoy Pismo Coast Village’s
VAST AMENITIES
Pismo Coast Village RV Resort has a full selection of amenities to make your visit as memorable as possible. From swimming in our heated pool to playing a round of miniature golf with your family, you are sure to remember your stay with us.
Explore All Our Amenities


Want to make your stay as memorable as possible?THINGS TO DO AT PISMO COAST VILLAGESurf CampCheck out the only major brand Surf Camp located in San Luis Obispo county and the only Surf Camp in Pismo Beach owned and operated by surfers from Pismo Beach.Pismo Beach ShoppingPismo Coast Village is located just a short walk from Downtown shopping. There you will find an assortment of shops for everyone. Gift shops, surf shops, art galleries, apparel, shoes, sandals and much more there are all within our downtown. Pismo BeachPismo State Beach offers all kinds of attractions: hiking, swimming, surf fishing, and digging for the famous Pismo clam.Wine TastingStay in Pismo Beach, where more than 20 wineries are located within a very short drive. Many of your favorite local wines can even be purchased right here in our General Store.














































